issue.title: V2 Framework Driver does not make use of passed in TestFilter

milestone.title: 3.0Beta1
milestone.description: First Beta release of NUnit 3.0. High- and normal-priority issues assigned to this milestone  need to be done before we can declare a beta. Low priority items will be postponed if necessary.

issue.body:
The V2 framework driver always calls the V2 core with an empty filter, no matter what has been passed to the run method.

This issue is being broken out from issue #517, which deals with the TestEventListener.

The TestFilter that is passed to the V2 driver is ignored and all tests are currently run.

This needs to be reviewed to see how much work is involved but if possible we should include it in the first beta release.
